To install Nodemcu Library in the Arduino IDE follow these steps :

1) Open IDE ---> Go to "file" on the left corner
2) Go to "Preference" ---> "Addition Boards Manager URLs" --->paste the below link there and press "ok"
3) Link : http://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package_esp8266com_index.json 
4) Go back to "Tools" ---> "Board" ---> "Board Manager"
5) You will see a window popup which automatically download the respective link
6) search for "esp8266" ---> it will show the library file ---> clink on it and install
7)That's it now you can change Arduino Uno board to Nodemcu
